    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pieces of furniture having hooks, used to receive  hats, coats, umbrellas, and scarves, and often having shelves, a seat, and mirror. Usually situated near the front door in the hall of the house. For upright postlike stands with pegs or hooks around the top, use "coat trees."</Note_Text>
